    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-06T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-06T04:00:00-05:00" n="680"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13114: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-06T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 6, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 6—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. Legation’s 226, May 29, 4 p.m.<note n="7" xml:id="d680fn7">Not
                        printed.</note> Vice Consul at Yunnanfu reports as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 5, 3 p.m. Reds captured Luting on June 1st and Tatsienlu on the
                            3rd. No information has been received concerning American citizens
                            resident at the latter place.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
